							<font face="Arial" size="2">
								Dear ENFM website visitor, <br>
								<br>
								We herewith like to inform you about the recent developments at ENFM. Unfortunately, we have to inform you that in October 2016, ENFM filed for bankruptcy. <br>
								<br>
								Badotherm Proces Instrumentatie B.V., also a pressure gauge manufacturer with its headquarters based in the Netherlands, has taken over a large part of the ENFM goodwill. 
								<a href="https://gallery.mailchimp.com/40dd0867cb6087847b62854cf/files/Information_Letter_Badotherm_and_ENFM.01.pdf" target="_blank"><span style='color:#007CC3'>Click here</span></a> to read the official statement and announcement of the bankruptcy and the goodwill transfer.<br>
								Next to that, we continue with several product lines, equipment &amp; toolings and the technical director to has joined our team. <br>
								Badotherm has at minimum the same high quality and service standards. We aim to deliver the same or better service and quality you are used to. Our main goal is to make the transition for you as seamless as possible.<br>
								<br>
								We will continue with products such as the high pressure gauge (up to 7000 bar), the pressure regulators, and sampling valves. Badotherm has decided to discontinue with the brass pressure gauge line, but we are able to offer you a competitive alternative in full stainless steel.<br><br>Want to know what we can do for you? <a href="http://www.badotherm.com/" target="_blank"><span style='color:#007CC3'>Visit our website</span></a> 
								for more information.
							</font>
